The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes a defensive framework based on collaborative multi-task training. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
